But there is hope. Covid-19 vaccines which have since been developed in the west will hopefully go a long way in reversing the ruins of the virus, when the vaccines become available.
If 2021 proves to be Covid-19’s waterloo, as we all hope, then sports venues across the world, which were mute for the better part of 2020, will once again reverberate with the familiar sounds of the fans.
End of football circus
For more than half a century, Kenyan football has been plagued by corrupt and incompetent administrators who have never been in short supply in this country.
Successive regimes have used Football Kenya Federation — and its innumerable predecessors — as a cash cow to the detriment of Kenyan football.
But the insolence of the current office-bearers has taken it to a whole new level.
Today, Kenyan football only exists by name; in truth, it’s on its deathbed.
Kenya to the world
Then of course 2021 could yet prove to be a memorable year for Kenyan sportsmen and women.
A number of sporting events which were initially lined up for 2020 will happen this year.
Top of the list is the Olympic Games in Tokyo, the returning WRC Safari Rally (since 2002) and the World Athletics Under-20 Championships in Nairobi. So much to look forward to. Happy New Year!



